# PR Comment Voice Profile

Use this template to define your personal PR comment voice. Fill in each section
based on patterns from your own real PR comments. The review skills (`review`,
`self-review`, `auto-review`) load `pr-voice.md` from this directory when writing
comments on your behalf.

To activate: copy this file to `pr-voice.md` in the same directory and fill it in.
`pr-voice.md` is gitignored — your voice stays local.

## How to generate your voice profile

Don't fill this in by hand -- let AI derive it from your actual PR comments.

Ask your AI assistant (Claude Code, Codex, etc.):

> Pull my PR review comments from the last year using `gh`, analyze the patterns,
> and fill in the pr-voice.md.example template. Save the result as pr-voice.md.

It will use `gh api` to fetch your comments across repos, identify recurring
patterns in tone, phrasing, and structure, and populate each section with real
examples from your history. Review the output and tweak anything that feels off,
but the LLM will catch patterns you wouldn't think to articulate yourself.

The more comments it pulls, the more accurate the profile. ~100+ comments across
multiple repos works well.

